HEADWORD: Byssine
<hw>Bys"sine</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>byssinus</ets> made of byssus, Gr. <grk>by`ssinos</grk> See
<er>Byssus</er>.]</ety> <def>Made of silk; having a silky or flaxlike
